#Text=Benn criticises concept of ' war on terror '
#Text=UK
#Text=Secretary of State for International Development

#Text=and deputy Labour leadership candidate Hilary Benn , has criticised US President George W. Bush 's ' war on terror ' concept in a speech given to the Center on International Cooperation , a US think tank .

#Text=Benn 's speech argued that the phrase ' war on terror ' should be deprecated because it ca n't be won by military means alone as well as indicating that the ' war-on-terror ' concept may have actually assisted terrorist groups by giving them a sense of belonging .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Benn criticises ' war on terror ' " — BBC News Online , April 16 , 2007
#Text=Reuters .
#Text=" UK minister rejects ' war on terror ' phrase " — CNN , April 16 , 2007
#Text=Sadr ministers leave al-Maliki 's cabinet

#Text=Six ministers in radical cleric Muqtada al-Sadr ' s Sadrist Movement have resigned from the Iraqi government , because Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki did not push for a timetable for the withdrawal of foreign troops from the country .

#Text=At a press conference , the head of Sadr 's parliamentary bloc Nassar Rubaie , read a statement from al-Sadr : " Considering the public interest , we found that it was necessary to issue an order to the ministers of the Sadr bloc to immediately withdraw from the Iraqi government , " The statement continued , "

#Text=Undercover reporter finds corruption and drugs at private prison

#Text=Investigations undertaken by an undercover journalist , unearthed corruption , intimidation of staff , as well as exposing issues concerning availability of drugs within HMP Rye Hill prison in Warwickshire , a class B facility which is privately run .
#Text=The investigative journalist finds staff living in fear of their lives and a massive black market in the prison which is run by GSL Group .
#Text=The company countered that the undercover reporter , did not follow his training as a guard .
#Text=BBC
#Text=' s
#Text=current affairs programme , Panorama , is scheduled to air an episode about the reporter 's findings .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Eric Allison .
#Text=" Drugs , bribe offers , staff in fear : life at Rye Hill jail " — The Guardian , April 16 , 2007
#Text=" Private prison failings exposed " — BBC News , Monday , 16 April 2007

#Text=UK 's Department of Trade and Industry may be restructured
#Text=Secretary of State for Trade and Industry
#Text=Alistair Darling
#Text=said that some MPs have called for the scrapping of Department of Trade and Industry ( DTI ) .
#Text=His statement came as a survey of 145 firms found that only 8 % saw the DTI playing an important role .
#Text=He has , however , said that DTI needed to continue for nuclear decommissioning .
#Text=A survey of British by the British Chamber of Commerce ( BCC ) found that British companies feel it more difficult to start and grow a business today than ten years ago .
#Text=On a positive note , of the top 750 European companies , UK companies generated a third of total profits .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" DTI ' may be heading for shake-up ' " — BBC News Online , April 16 , 2007
#Text=Ashley Seager .
#Text=" Business leaders say climate for startups worse than 10 years ago " — The Guardian , April 16 , 2007

column1: #Text=Pipeline firms consolidate in Russia
#Text=According to Russian officials , Transneft and Transnefteprodukt(TNP ) are to merge .
#Text=The merger will create a " single network of oil and oil products via the pipelines and protect the economic interests of the Russian Federation , " according to a Kremlin Statement .
#Text=The move would give the companies concerned more power internationally , say analysts .
#Text=President Vladimir Putin has signed a decree , approving the merger .
#Text=The Russian government would keep a 75 % ownership stake in the combined firm .
#Text=The merger of firms is to be complete in five months .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Putin Signs Pipeline Firms Merger " — The Moscow Times , April 17 , 2007

#Text=US still seeking missing ex-FBI agent in Iran
#Text=For the third time in a month , the United States has requested information about a missing former FBI agent believed to be in Iran .
#Text=The State Department says Robert Levinson went missing while visiting Kish Island in March .
#Text=He is retired and is said to have been there on his own business interests .
#Text=Iran 's previous responses have been to request more information about Levinson .
#Text=Each time , the inquiries went through Swiss diplomats .
